review_title: Good socks - plain, comfortable, and sturdy.
reviews: No complaints. There are a variety of similar sock options to choose from on Amazon, so looking for a combination of cost, plain unpatterned black, and good quality socks I elected to take a chance on these. At first I didn't like them because they felt so much thinner than the cheap walmart cotton socks I'm used to, as I feared the thin material meant they would quickly develop holes. However, I've since determined that despite the thinner material, they seem to be well made and sturdy. I bought 6 packs, so I can go about 5 weeks before I need to wash a load. Worth the price in my opinion. Best part is that I never have to worry about matching socks, since now they are all the same kind! I'm a 12Wide though, and I think by the time you hit a size 13-14 mens these might be a bit more snug than some might like.

reviews:
I just received these, puy them on, and I'm already seeing my skin right through the fabric. Its a little hard to see in the picture but a lot more noticeable in person. Not sure why other reviewers are raving about these. Pure trash.

EDIT: I'm adding more to this.
- The socks are very uncomfortable and scratchy. I thought this would go away after a wash but it's not the case.
- As others have also mentioned, these are not big enough. I wear a size 11 and these feel far too small on me (as if I just put on my girlfriend's socks by mistake).
- The socks are also very low so if you sit down you will show some leg. Certainly not good enough for a dress sock.

reviews: Bought these in Feb. 2020. The socks were on the small size when new. They shrank after the first wash quite a bit and seem to get smaller with each wash. Also, although I have no way to measuring this, it seems that the cotton content is a lot less than the claimed 88% (comparing to another brand that is 80% cotton, these seem a lot more "plasticy". Not recommended.
